com.apriori.di

Annotation Type Calls


  • @Target(value=METHOD)
 @Retention(value=RUNTIME)
 @Documented
public @interface Calls
    A marker for an injectable wrapper method. The method should not be static and should be abstract. A concrete version of the function will be generated in the injection entry point. If the function has arguments, they should have the same types and qualifier annotations as the called method's injection dependencies. Any other dependencies not found in the argument list will be automatically injected.

    • Required Element Summary

      Required Elements 
      Modifier and Type Required Element and Description
      String value
      The name of the method that will be called in the generated injection entry point.

    • Element Detail

      • value

        public abstract String value
        The name of the method that will be called in the generated injection entry point. The name should be specified in the same syntax as used by javadoc {@link}s with the one exception that inner classes should be denoted using dollar signs ($) instead of dots (as if referencing the class name for use in Class.forName(String)). As in javadoc, a hash (#) should be used to separate the class from the method. Types in the parameter list do not need to be fully-qualified as long as no ambiguity results from using short names. The parameter list can be left out completely if the named method is not overloaded. A value that begins with a hash is assumed to be a member of the current class (just like in javadoc).
